1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:05,550
Groundwater lagging is not just a time shift.

2
00:00:05,550 --> 00:00:10,700
Lagging Theory focuses on flux-gradient asynchrony.

3
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:16,900
Gradient and flux can evolve on different response time scales.

4
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:26,050
Storage, drainage, leakage, flow paths, domain exchange, and coupling can all create delayed response.

5
00:00:26,050 --> 00:00:32,450
A fitted curve can still transfer the wrong hydraulic parameter.

6
00:00:32,450 --> 00:00:40,700
The engineering test is whether delayed response changes pumping limits, recovery time, or a design threshold.

7
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:45,800
Lagging Theory turns delayed hydraulic response into a decision test.
